{"parse":{"title":"Purpose-centered education","pageid":5924318,"revid":852855647,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Purpose-centered education</b> (PCE) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Pedagogy\" title=\"Pedagogy\">pedagogical</a> model developed by <a href=\"/wiki/Audrey_Cohen\" title=\"Audrey Cohen\">Audrey Cohen</a> and her colleagues at the College for Human Services, now <a href=\"/wiki/Metropolitan_College_of_New_York\" title=\"Metropolitan College of New York\">Metropolitan College of New York</a>, PCE blends theory and practice in students\u2019 jobs and lives to produce graduates with a guiding vision of social justice and continues to  underlie the development of the curriculum at Metropolitan College of New York.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Purpose-centered_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Ardovini, Joanne. &amp; Anne Lopes (April 2009). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://transformativestudies.org/wp-content/uploads/103798tia1937-023709003.pdf\">\u201cTeaching Social Justice: A Proposal to Innovate the Liberal Arts Core\"</a>, Theory in Action, Volume 2:2.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Purpose-centered_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.metropolitan.edu/about/history1.php\">Metropolitan College of New York Web site</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.certificationpoint.org/stud